.TH INDEX 3F
.SH NAME
index \- return location of \s-1FORTRAN\s+1 substring
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B "character\(**N1 ch1"
.B "character\(**N2 ch2"
.B "integer i"
.P
.B "i = index(ch1, ch2)"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Index\^
returns the location of substring
.I ch2\^
in string
.IR ch1 .
The value returned is the position at which substring
.I ch2\^
starts, or 0 if it is not present in string
.IR ch1 .
If N2 is greater than N1, a zero is returned.
